events.name: Google DevFest 2014
events.description:
Hello everybody!

We are pleased to announce the Google DevFest 2014! This year the event will be regarding wearables and we are holding a hackathon around this topic. The event is completely free, so feel free to come with your friends or colleagues regardless of your background. The agenda for the event will be the following one:

10:00 - Arrival and registration

10:40 - Introductory presentation

11:40 - Break for lunch

12:30 - Hack time

17:00 - Coffee break + status update

20:00 - Prizes

20:30 - Closing

We will have smartwatches for the winners of the hackathon, so bring your idea and be ready to hack it!

events.name: Crazy ideas for 2015!!
events.description:
The end of the year is getting really close so let's discuss ideas for the upcoming 2015!

We'd like to hear your ideas over a drink. Also, if you want to help us organizing the events, please let us know. You're welcome even if you just wanna hear what's coming!

If you can't attend but would like to propose some events or can help us just drop me a Meetup message or mail ([masked]).

We're also looking for companies that would like to sponsor us by offering space/drinks for the events. We're interested in hearing what cool projects your company is working on, too.

Hyvää joulua,

Ramon
events.how_to_find_us: Just look for me to find the table. You can also send me a message through meetup, mail (oni.pool@gmail.com) or hangouts if you can't find us.

events.name: Android Study Jam
events.description:
Between February 1 and March 31 we would like to host a weekly study group for the Udacity Android Fundamentals course (https://www.udacity.com/course/ud853).

This is an introductory course to Android but it's quite dense and the contents come directly from Google Android Engineers (the quality of the content is really good). I think that even if you're a professional Android developer there's something you will learn.
Previous Java knowledge is highly recommended but experience in any other programming language should be enough.

There will be 7 sessions, 1 following each lesson (6 lessons) + 1 final session to share the project.

You will get access to the contents of the Udacity course, free in-person guidance & tutoring, some swag.
events.how_to_find_us: Here's the map https://goo.gl/maps/TJn8i and you can reach me at +358503202380

We are meeting this Thursday in Kaisla to discuss more about the events and meetups for 2016 and the future of the community. events.name: First-hand insights from Google I/O 2016
events.description:
Three members of this community were in Mountain View last month at Google I/O.

Let's hear the first-hand experience from Eva Rio (Service & UX Designer at Tuxera), Jerry Jalava (GDE and Senior System Architect at Qvik) and Jon Imanol Durán (Senior Software Engineer at Zalando) as well as discuss what were the highlights regarding Design/UX, Cloud and Android.

Qvik will be hosting this event. Qvik is a Google partner, that provides business-driven mobile services and digital solutions. They also creates highly scalable backends utilizing cloud infrastructures.

• 17.45 Tommy Eklund - CTO Choicely / Qvik - From App Engine through Firebase into Big Query and forward unto Machine Learning

Next ‘17 will be the largest cloud event in Google's history. Google Cloud engineers, customers and partners will gather for inspiration and hands on experiences with tools, technologies and services born in the Cloud, including the latest developments from Google Cloud Platform, G Suite, Maps and Devices.

events.name: Google I/O '17 Extended
events.description:
Join us at Zalando's Helsinki Tech Hub for a night of Google madness!

Here's your chance to come and view the Google I/O keynote on a big screen with like-minded people. In addition to the keynote, we have organised some cool activities (more about this below) to pass the time until the keynote begins. Some snacks and drinks will also be provided.

Doors open at 18:00 and the keynote is scheduled at 20:00 Finnish time.

Between 18:00 and 20:00 there will be three hands-on labs you can join:

- Kotlin Koans:
  Learn Kotlin by doing small exercises. Hosted by Ilya Zorin (Android Engineer - Zalando).
  Requirements: laptop.

- App Engine:
  Introduction to App Engine by deploying your first service. Hosted by Jon Duran (Android Engineer - Zalando)
  Requirements: laptop with Java SE Development Kit 8 (JDK 8) and IntelliJ Community Edition.

- Firebase for Android:
  Build a real-time chat client using Firebase on Android. Hosted by Ramon Sadornil (Android Engineer - Amer Sports)
  Requirements: laptop with Android Studio and an Android phone (or emulator).
events.how_to_find_us: Zalando Finland Oy // Runeberginkatu 5 D, 00100 Helsinki, Finland

events.name: A Flutterful Evening
events.description:
Hold your horses! GDG Helsinki is gonna have a Flutter Evening!

In this month of May, our megawesome friends from Codemate will be opening their doors for us to have a delightful time together to talk about Flutter! \o/

If you haven't heard about Flutter yet, in a nutshell, Flutter is a mobile app SDK to build native apps for Android and iOS with a shared codebase. It uses Dart as its core development language. Flutter has been developed by and internally used by Google, along with other companies.

Your initial reaction might be something along the lines of "oh no, yet another cross-platform framework?!". We know how you feel, but hold on! Come and check why Flutter has been a recent groundbreaking tech in the mobile development ecosystem.

More info about Flutter here: https://flutter.io/

// AGENDA:

- 17:00: Doors open, food, and networking

- 17:30: Welcome from Hosts

- 17:45: Hot reloading your apps to life - Iiro Krankka (https://twitter.com/koorankka)

- 18:25: Short break

- 18:55: Reactive Flutter with Streams and RxDart - Brian Egan
(https://twitter.com/brianegan)

- 19:35: A freeform Q&A session with speakers - ask about Flutter and you shall be answered

- 20:05: End

// IMPORTANT TO KNOW:

1) Confirmations with information (first + last name) missing won't participate in the lottery at the end of the event. Check your information here and please update it!
2) If you are not going please don't confirm it. Doing that you gonna give the opportunity to the interested people to join :)
3) We won't organize the list again, once the list of attendees is closed is closed.

events.name: Cloud Study Jam - GCP Essentials
events.description:
GDG Cloud Helsinki and GDG Helsinki is organising Cloud Study Jam.

****READ THIS****
In our first Study Jam we are concentrating on beginners with GCP Essentials. So if you are already familiar with GCP this not for you, we will have other more advanced study jams later.

****KEEP READING****
At the event we’ll use a tool called Qwiklabs, a Google training product. If you have used Qwiklabs before, great! Make sure you know your password. If you have never used Qwiklabs before, save time by creating an account for yourself prior to the class at:
https://google.qwiklabs.com/users/sign_up

(creating an account is free).

At the event we will give you a link for free Qwiklabs access. Make sure you check the opt-in box for promos! That makes you eligible for additional free access after you complete the first series of labs.

****STILL KEEP READING****
What to bring to the event:
- Laptop -- Mac, PC, Chromebook, Linux, everyone’s welcome.
- Laptop charger.
- The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, use Firefox or Chrome.

Looking forward to seeing you at the event!

Schedule:

17:00 - Doors open & some snacks
17:30 - Study Jam Time
20:00 - Doors close

ps. places are very limited, so release your place if you can't make it.
pps. if this event is super popular we can run more GCP Essentials jams in the future.

events.name: #Hack19: International Flutter Hackathon
events.description:
Join us on Saturday, June 1st, 2019 for the first-ever all-day International Flutter Hackathon organized by over 2 dozen communities worldwide.
Join a team of 2-5 fellow developers at your location to build something amazing in #Flutter and #Hummingbird. At the end of the event, all participants will vote on their favorite projects and the winners will receive prizes and bragging rights 😎 ✌️

For more information visit:
https://flutterhackathon.com/

Some IMPORTANT info about the Hackathon and what's gonna happen. Please read it.

1) Will there be food? YES! \o/... Codemate is also sponsoring that to make sure we won't be distracted by our empty tummies.

2) The theme of the hackathon will be announced at the beginning of the event.

3) No solo teams. A team must consist of at least 2 people.

4) The code should be hosted in a public repository (Bitbucket, Github, etc).

5) The project must be completed by the end of your hackathon.

6) Just 1 project will be chosen by organizers to participate in a global Flutter contest to compete with other hubs that are organizing this same event. After the event, all participants will vote. Votes are due by end of day Sunday, June 2 (UTC). More info on how to vote to follow, there will be a website for that (made with Flutter Web, ofc).

7) Please please please, have Flutter already installed in your machine. Here some "Getting Started" info on how to do it: https://flutterhackathon.com/#getting-started or Flutter docs: https://flutter.dev/docs/get-started/install
